        <dt>Identification and Creation</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
            <dt>Object Number</dt>
            <dd>1960.487</dd>

            
                            <dt>Title</dt>
                <dd>Razor</dd>
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                  <dt>Other Titles</dt>
                    <dd>
                                                                                                                                      Alternate Title: Villanovan razor                                                                        </dd>
                            
                            <dt>Classification</dt>
                <dd>Tools and Equipment</dd>
                                        <dt>Work Type</dt>
                <dd>
                                                            razor                                                      </dd>
                                        <dt>Date</dt>
                <dd>8th century BCE</dd>
                                        <dt>Places</dt>
                <dd>
                                                            Creation Place: Ancient & Byzantine World, Europe, Tarquinia (Etruria)                                                      </dd>
                                        <dt>Period</dt>
                <dd>Orientalizing period</dd>
                                        <dt>Culture</dt>
                <dd>Italic</dd>
                            <dt>Persistent Link</dt>
                <dd><a href="https://hvrd.art/o/311123">https://hvrd.art/o/311123</a></dd>
          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                <dt>Physical Descriptions</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Bronze</dd>
            
           
                        <dt>Technique</dt>
             <dd>Cast and hammered</dd>
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>9.3 cm (3 11/16 in.)</dd>
            
                          <dt>Technical Details</dt>
              <dd>
                                                      <p class="divider">Chemical Composition: XRF data from Tracer<br />
Alloy: Bronze<br />
Alloying Elements: copper, tin<br />
Other Elements: lead, iron, antimony, arsenic<br />
<br />
K. Eremin, January 2014</p>
                                      <p class="divider">Technical Observations: The patina is brown with green corrosion. There are losses along the outer curved cutting edge.<br />
 <br />
Because there is no apparent join, the razor was probably made by casting the handle from which an excess of metal to be used as a blank protruded. This excess metal was then hammered out to form the blade, with annealing done as needed to keep the metal malleable yet strong enough to be able to be sharpened. Surface decoration on the blade was done by engraving. The swastika and two geometric designs on the blade were engraved relatively shallowly, as there is no evidence of them on the reverse. <br />
 <br />
 <br />
Carol Snow (submitted 2002)</p>
                                                </dd>
            
            
            
            
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
